{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-post-template-tsx","path":"/posts/time-to-play-with-docker/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"d07d54da-5426-5ec3-ae07-ca9fc136e48e","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4aaa1d60e83ff887717aab0e710ed7b2/4b190/docker.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/4aaa1d60e83ff887717aab0e710ed7b2/8ac56/docker.webp 240w,\n/static/4aaa1d60e83ff887717aab0e710ed7b2/d3be9/docker.webp 480w,\n/static/4aaa1d60e83ff887717aab0e710ed7b2/d00b9/docker.webp 800w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/4aaa1d60e83ff887717aab0e710ed7b2/09b79/docker.jpg 240w,\n/static/4aaa1d60e83ff887717aab0e710ed7b2/7cc5e/docker.jpg 480w,\n/static/4aaa1d60e83ff887717aab0e710ed7b2/4b190/docker.jpg 800w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/4aaa1d60e83ff887717aab0e710ed7b2/4b190/docker.jpg\"\n            alt=\"docker\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>In the field of virtualization, <strong>Docker</strong> is a great tool which is very lightweight compared to the triditional virtual machines. It enables you to separate your applications from your infrastructure so you can deliver software quickly. With Docker, you can manage your infrastructure in the same ways you manage your applications. By taking advantage of Docker’s methodologies for shipping, testing, and deploying code, you can significantly reduce the delay between writing code and running it in production.</p>\n<p>To start the journey with Docker, first, we need to install Docker on our machine. The community version of Docker is free and open-source, and it’s available for most of the operating systems like Linux, Windows, and macOS.</p>\n<h2 id=\"official-installation-instructions\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#official-installation-instructions\" aria-label=\"official installation instructions permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Official Installation Instructions</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.docker.com/desktop/install/linux\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Install Docker on Linux</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.docker.com/desktop/install/mac-install\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Install Docker on macOS</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.docker.com/desktop/install/windows-install\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Install Docker on Windows</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"useful-docker-commands\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#useful-docker-commands\" aria-label=\"useful docker commands permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Useful Docker Commands</h2>\n<p>After installing Docker, you can start playing with it. Here are some basic example commands in daily use. More commands can be found in the <a href=\"https://docs.docker.com/engine/reference/commandline/docker\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">official documentation</a>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"whole-system\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#whole-system\" aria-label=\"whole system permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>whole system</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">docker login</code> - Log in to a Docker registry</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">docker info</code> - Display system-wide information</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">docker version</code> - Show the Docker version information</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"images\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#images\" aria-label=\"images permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>images</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">docker images</code> - List images</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">docker rmi</code> - Remove one or more images</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">docker pull</code> - Pull an image or a repository from a registry</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">docker push</code> - Push an image or a repository to a registry</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">docker build</code> - Build an image from a Dockerfile</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"containers\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#containers\" aria-label=\"containers permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>containers</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">docker ps</code> - List containers</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">docker run</code> - Run a command in a new container</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">docker kill</code> - Kill one or more running containers</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">docker exec</code> - Run a command in a running container</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">docker commit</code> - Create a new image from a container’s changes</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">docker cp</code> - Copy files/folders between a container and the local filesystem</li>\n</ul>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/2017-07-20---Time-to-Play-with-Docker//posts/time-to-play-with-docker","tagSlugs":["/tag/virtualization/","/tag/docker/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2017-07-20T18:45:00.000Z","description":"docker is a great tool for virtualization, it's a lightweight alternative to virtual machines.","tags":["Virtualization","Docker"],"title":"Time to Play with Docker","socialImage":{"publicURL":"/static/4aaa1d60e83ff887717aab0e710ed7b2/docker.jpg"}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/2017-07-20---Time-to-Play-with-Docker//posts/time-to-play-with-docker"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","288581551","401334301"],"slicesMap":{}}